2 HOUSE BILL 998
1 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
2 12–102.
3 This title applies only in Baltimore City.
4 12–1604.
5 (a) This section applies only to the 46th alcoholic beverages district, which at all
6 times is coterminous with the 46th legislative district in the Legislative Districting Plan of
7 2022.
8 (K) THE BOARD MAY AUTHORIZE THE TRANSFER OF A CLASS B–D–7
9 LICENSE FROM THE 700 BLOCK OF WASHINGTON BOULEVARD IN THE 40TH
10 ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES DISTRICT FOR USE BY AN ESTABLISHMENT ON THE 200
11 BLOCK OF SOUTH HIGH STREET IN THE 46TH ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES DISTRICT.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, notwithstanding §§ 6–308
13 and 6–311 of the Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis Article, a licensed establishment on
14 the south side of the unit block of West Pratt Street may keep and allow individuals to
15 consume on the licensed premises alcoholic beverages donated by a manufacturer or
16 wholesaler if:
17 (1) the alcoholic beverages are donated and served at an event for which a
18 nonprofit entity has rented the licensed premises;
19 (2) the licensee has provided to the Board of License Commissioners for
20 Baltimore City evidence of the nonprofit status of the entity renting the licensed premises;
21 (3) the licensee serves the alcohol donated for the event;
22 (4) any related taxes have been remitted; and
23 (5) the licensee only keeps and serves alcoholic beverages in conjunction
24 with a single rental contract.
25 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, notwithstanding § 12–2202
26 of the Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis Article, a Class B–D–7 beer, wine, and liquor
27 license issued for a premises in the 1600 block of Eastern Avenue shall be considered
28 unexpired until the end of July 1, 2027, for the purpose of being renewed to the current
29 license year and transferred to a new owner at a premises in the 700 block of Aliceanna
30 Street.
31 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
32 1, 2026. Section 2 of this Act shall remain effective for a period of 2 years and, at the end of

HOUSE BILL 998 3
1 May 31, 2028, Section 2 of this Act, with no further action required by the General
2 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
